# Product Requirements Document — NBA Stats Explorer

**Product Name:** NBA Stats Explorer  
**Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** June 2026  
**Status:** Draft  
**Owner:** Product Team  

---

## 1. Overview

### 1.1 Purpose

NBA Stats Explorer is a web application that gives basketball fans, analysts, and developers instant access to the complete historical record of NBA statistics — every player, every game, and every season from 1946 to the present — powered by the balldontlie.io API.

### 1.2 Problem Statement

Basketball enthusiasts and analysts currently have no single, easy-to-use interface that aggregates the full depth of NBA history. Official sources are fragmented, paywalled, or require technical knowledge to query. There is a need for a clean, accessible tool that surfaces player statistics, season averages, and game results without friction.

### 1.3 Goals

- Provide access to every NBA player ever recorded, active or retired.
- Surface per-game and season-average statistics for any player in any season.
- Display every game result from 1946–47 to the current season.
- Deliver a fast, intuitive interface requiring zero setup beyond an API key.

### 1.4 Non-Goals

- The app will not support user accounts, saved searches, or personalisation in v1.
- The app will not cover leagues other than NBA (WNBA, G-League, international) in v1.
- The app will not stream live play-by-play data in v1.
- The app will not provide betting odds or fantasy integrations in v1.

