## 3. Features and Requirements

### 3.1 API Key Management

**Priority:** P0 — Must Have

- The user must be able to enter their balldontlie.io API key into a persistent input field.
- The app must display a connection status indicator (connected / error / not set).
- The key must be used as the `Authorization` header on every API request.
- The key must not be logged or transmitted to any third-party service.
- If no key is present and a data request is made, the app must surface a clear prompt to add one.

### 3.2 Player Search

**Priority:** P0 — Must Have

- Users can search for any player by name (full or partial).
- Results display: player name, position, height, weight, current or last team.
- Results are paginated with next/previous controls using cursor-based pagination.
- Clicking a player opens their detail view.
- Search is triggered by button click or pressing Enter.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Returns results for active and retired players.
- Handles partial name matches (e.g. "Bron" returns LeBron James).
- Shows a clear empty state when no results are found.
- Shows a loading indicator while the request is in flight.

### 3.3 Player Detail View

**Priority:** P0 — Must Have

- From a player's profile, the user can select any season from 1946 to the current year.
- The app fetches and displays season averages: points, rebounds, assists, steals, blocks, turnovers, FG%, 3PT%, FT%, minutes per game, and games played.
- The app also fetches and displays the 10 most recent game logs for that season, showing the same stat columns plus +/-.
- A back button returns the user to the search results without losing their query.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Season selector defaults to the most recent season.
- Displays a "no data" message if the player has no averages for the selected season.
- Game log dates are formatted as YYYY-MM-DD.

### 3.4 Season Averages Tab

**Priority:** P0 — Must Have

- Dedicated tab where users type a player name and select a season.
- If multiple players match the name, a picker is shown to disambiguate.
- If exactly one match, stats load immediately.
- Stats are displayed in a stat-card grid format.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Picker appears when 2 or more players share a similar name.
- Single-match queries bypass the picker entirely.
- Displays season label (e.g. 2024–25) alongside the player name.

### 3.5 Games Browser

**Priority:** P0 — Must Have

- Users can browse game results filtered by season (1946–present), game type (regular season or playoffs), and optional team name.
- Results display: date, matchup, final score, season, game type.
- Results are paginated.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Season selector covers every NBA season since 1946.
- Team filter is client-side string matching on team name and abbreviation.
- Playoff games are visually distinguished from regular season.
- Score is displayed only when the game has been played (not for scheduled future games).

