## 5. Data Model

### Player object (from API)
```
id, first_name, last_name, position, height, weight, jersey_number, team { id, full_name, abbreviation }
```

### Season average object (from API)
```
player_id, season, games_played, min, pts, reb, ast, stl, blk, turnover,
fg_pct, fg3_pct, ft_pct
```

### Per-game stat object (from API)
```
player { id, first_name, last_name }, game { id, date, season },
team { abbreviation }, min, pts, reb, ast, stl, blk, turnover,
fg_pct, fg3_pct, ft_pct, plus_minus
```

### Game object (from API)
```
id, date, season, postseason, status,
home_team { full_name, abbreviation }, home_team_score,
visitor_team { full_name, abbreviation }, visitor_team_score
```

